The paper deals with the problem of recovering a signal from a set of noisy linear projections, which is a common problem in signal processing and information theory. The paper also establishes a duality between the problem of unlabeled ordered sampling (UOS) and compressed sensing (CS), which are both active areas of research in CS. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.IT (Information Theory), which deals with the fundamental limits of communication and information processing. The paper also proposes a low-complexity algorithm for signal recovery, which falls under the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), signal processing (cs.SP), matrix methods (cs.MM), and statistical learning (cs.SI).
